        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 6 at 6:40PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 640 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Culverton, or near
Sparta, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Warrenton, Sparta, Mitchell, Shoals, Jewell, Beall Springs, Mayfield,
and Culverton.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
